President Obama made several phone calls regarding the Afghan elections. He expressed his appreciation to President Karzai for accepting the certification of the first round election results and agreeing to a second round of voting. President Obama emphasized that this decision was in the best interests of the Afghan people and reiterated the United States' commitment to an outcome that reflects their will. He also called Dr. Abdullah Abdullah to appreciate his constructive efforts. President Obama received an update from Ambassador Einkenberry on the developments related to the Afghan elections and thanked him and his team for their hard work. He also discussed his appreciation for Senator John Kerry's collaboration with the Ambassador.